This paper discusses a caching and routing strategy for information-centric networks using reinforcement learning. The topic of information-centric networks is closely related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and the use of reinforcement learning suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses performance and scalability challenges, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of reinforcement learning for optimization could also fall under control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of caching and routing, which could fall under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
